xresponse installation instructions
====================================

1. Compiling from sources
-------------------------

1.1 Dependencies
----------------

The following packages must be installed before compiling xresponse:
  autoconf(>=2.67), automake(>=1.11), pkg-config(>=0.25), libglib2.0-dev(>=2.24.2),
  libx11-dev(>=2:1.3.3), libxdamage-dev(1:1.1.3>=), libxfixes-dev(1:4.0.5>=),
  libxtst-dev(>=2:1.1.0), libxext-dev(>=2:1.1.2), libxi-dev(>=2:1.3)
  
Note that earlier versions might also work.


1.2 Compilation & Installation
------------------------------

To compile xresponse extract the source archive and do the following
steps in the xresponse directory:

  1) Greate configuration file with "autoreconf -fi"
  2) Create makefile with "./configure"
     The configure tool accepts standard parameters (like installation 
     directory etc.). Try "./configure --help to see all options. 
  3) Build the xresponse binaries with "make"
  4) Install the bult binaries with "make install"
  

